    # session nested in shpool (both set) switches the tmux client in place and
    # must stay -- gate on "in shpool, not in tmux". A cancelled picker (ESC)
    # returns non-zero, so the exit guard's `test $rc -eq 0` fails and we stay
    # put. csp forces shpool, so it detaches whenever we're in a shpool session
    # regardless of tmux. Capture the picker's status and run the exit guard
